#MEM id=storytelling source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/lena/skills/marketplace/storytelling/SKILL.md savings=0%
M||tx|---
M||name|storytelling
M||desc|Use when crafting narratives that connect pd value to cs pain through clear setup-conflict-resolution arcs.
M||tx|---
M|When|it|Need cohesive narrative for cg, pd launches, or decks.
M|When|it|Translating tc capabilities into relatable cs stories.
M|When|it|Coaching spokespeople or SDRs on better pitch storytelling.
M|Fram|tx|1. **Audience & Conflict** – identify who the hero is (cs persona) and what obstacle they face.
M|Fram|tx|2. **Story Arc (SCAR)** – Situation → Complication → Action → Resolution.
M|Fram|tx|3. **Characterization** – give personas motives, stakes, and quotes.
M|Fram|tx|4. **Sensory Detail** – use vivid language, specific metrics, and concrete examples.
M|Fram|tx|5. **Moral/CTA** – tie resolution back to pd value and explicit nx step.
M|Temp|it|Narrative outline (hook, scene, rising tension, turn, resolution, CTA).
M|Temp|- Pi|
M|Temp|tx|```
M|Temp|tx|"Most {persona}s today face {pain}. When {trigger}, {impact}. We worked w/ {cs} to {action}, leading to {result}."
M|Temp|tx|```
M|Temp|it|Story inventory tracker to log cs, industry, proof points.
M|Tips|it|Record cs interviews to capture natural phrasing for quotes.
M|Tips|it|Swap metaphors/analogies per persona so stories feel tailored.
M|Tips|it|Reinforce numbers w/ vivid imagery (e.g., "saved hours = extra sprints delivered").
M|Tips|it|Align every story w/ the current positioning doc to avoid mixed messages.